definition.value: A cholestanoid that is 7-dehydrocholesterol carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at position 24 (24S-stereoisomer).
A cholestanoid that is 5alpha-cholestan-3beta-ol carrying an additional oxo substituent at position 7.
A cholestanoid that is lathosterol in which the double bond at position 7,8 has been oxidised to the corresponding epoxide (the 7alpha,8alpha stereoisomer).

A pyrrolopyrazole that is 5,6-dihydro-4H-pyrrolo[1,2-b]pyrazole which is substituted at positions 2 and 3 by 6-methylpyridin-2-yl and 6-(aminocarbonyl)quinolin-4-yl groups, respectively. A Transforming growth factor-betaRI (TGF-betaRI) kinase inhibitor, it blocks TGF-beta-mediated tumor growth in glioblastoma.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc by loss of two protons, one from each of its sulfo and carboxy groups.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-GlcNAc.
A beta-D-galactoside that is the 4-methoxyphenyl glycoside of a disaccharide consisting of a 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid residue linked (1->3) to beta-D-galactose.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-OMe by loss of two protons, one from each of its sulfo and carboxy groups.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-OMe.
A beta-D-galactoside that is the 4-methoxyphenyl glycoside of a disaccharide consisting of a beta-D-glucuronic acid residue linked (1->3) to beta-D-galactose.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-OMe by loss of a proton from its carboxy group.
An organic sodium salt that is the monosodium salt of beta-D-GlcA-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-OMe.
A beta-D-galactoside that is the 4-[2-(4-sulfanylbutanamido)ethyl]phenyl glycoside of a disaccharide consisting of a 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid residue linked (1->3) to beta-D-galactose.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-[CH2]2NHC(O)[CH2]3SH by loss of two protons, one from each of its sulfo and carboxy groups.
An androstanoid that is testosterone carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at the 1beta-position. A metabolite of testosterone.
An androstanoid that is testosterone carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at the 2beta-position.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OC6H4-4-[CH2]2NHC(O)[CH2]3SH.
Any compound that inihibits the mammalian protein, eukaryotic initiation factor 4F.

A random copolymer based on poly-L-lysine containing a disaccharide glycomimetic of the natural HNK-1 (human natural killer-1) glycoepitope. The proportions of the HNK-1 glycomimetic-modified poly-L-lysine component and the unmodified poly-L-lysine component (labelled m and m respectively in the diagram) are respectively x% and (100-x)%.
A ruthenium coordination entity that acts as a water-soluble carbon monoxide-releasing molecule.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the hydroxy group of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of oleic acid with the hydroxy group of 13-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with the hydroxy group of 9-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with the hydroxy group of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with the hydroxy group of 13-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A beta-D-galactoside that is the methyl glycoside of a disaccharide consisting of a 3-O-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronic acid residue linked (1->3) to beta-D-galactose.
The carbohydrate acid derivative anion formed from beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OMe by loss of two protons, one from each of its sulfo and carboxy groups.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of octadecanoic acid with the hydroxy group of 12-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of beta-D-GlcA3S-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-OMe.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of octadecanoic acid with the hydroxy group of 13-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of octadecanoic acid with the hydroxy group of 9-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-hexadecenoic acid with the hydroxy group of 5-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of (9Z)-octadecenoic acid with the hydroxy group of 5-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 5,6-epoxy-(8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid.
A ketogluconate that is the conjugate base of 5-dehydro-L-gluconic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group. Major microspecies at pH 7.3
A ketoaldonic acid phosphate consisting of (2xi)-3-deoxy-beta-D-threo-hept-6-ulopyranosonic acid carrying a single phospho substituent at position 7.
An acyl monophosphate(1-) that is the conjugate base of acetyl dihydrogen phosphate.

A 3-oxo-5alpha-steroid that is 5alpha-estrane which is substituted by an oxo group at position 3, a hydroxy group at the 17beta position, and which has a double bond between positions 1 and 10. It is a 19-norsteroid arising from successive oxidation of dihydrotestosterone at C19.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 5-hydroxy-(6E,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoic acid.
